                     <title type="complete" ref="LIT2701Dawit">Dāwit ‘Psalter’</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                     
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="2r" to="189r"/>
                        <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit ‘Psalms of David’</title>
                        <note>The following Psalms are wrongly numbered: Psalm 15: ፲፮, 141: ፻፵. Psalms 90 and 100 are not numbered at all.</note>
                        <explicit xml:lang="gez" type="supplication">
                           <locus target="#122v">f. 122v, after Psalm 100</locus>
                        <quote xml:lang="gez"><hi rend="rubric">ሰአሊ፡ ለነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ማርያም፡ ምሕረተ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልድኪ፡ የሐውጸነ፡ እምአርያም፡ ኦአምላከ፡ ዳዊት፡ አድኅነነ፡ እምዕለት፡ እኪት፡ ወባልሐነ፡ እምኵሉ፡
                           እመንሱት፡ እለ፡ ወለዱነ፡ በሥጋ፡ ወእለ፡ ሐጸኑነ፡ በመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ኅቡረ፡ ይምሐሮሙ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ኦእግዚኦ፡ ዕቀቦ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ገብረ፡  <supplied reason="lost">እግዚእ፡</supplied> አዕርፍ፡ እግዚኦ፡ ነፍሰ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ <supplied reason="lost">እግዚእ፡</supplied></hi></quote>
                           <note>The name of <persName ref="PRS15304GabraEgzi"><roleName type="title">ʾAbuna</roleName> Gabra ʾƎgziʾ</persName> was written twice 
                              by a secondary hand in reddish-brown ink and then partly erased.</note>
                        </explicit>
                        <colophon xml:lang="gez" xml:id="coloph1">
                              <locus target="#189v"/>
                           <hi rend="rubric">ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘአቡነ፡ <supplied reason="lost">ንዋየ፡</supplied> ሥ<supplied reason="lost">ላሴ፡</supplied> ዘወሀቦ፡
                                 ለወልደ አብ። ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ለዓለም፡ ወለዓለም፡ ዐለም፡ ሰዓሊ፡ ለነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ማርያም። ምሕረተ፡
                                 ክርስቶስ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MV"/> ኦእግዚኦ፡ ዕቀቦ፡ ለአቡነ፡ <supplied reason="lost">ገብረ፡ እግዚእ</supplied>፡</hi> 
                           <note>It is written at the end of the present text in red ink. The name of <persName role="donor" ref="PRS15303NewayaSellase"><roleName type="title">ʾAbuna</roleName>
                              Nǝwāya Śǝllāse</persName> and the last line of the supplication have been erased. 
                              The supplication prayer is almost identical to the supplication quoted above. The name of a later supplicant, <persName ref="PRS15304GabraEgzi"><roleName type="title">ʾAbuna</roleName> Gabra ʾƎgziʾ</persName>, 
                              is partly erased and is written in the same secondary hand as in the supplication above, in reddish-brown ink.</note>
                        </colophon>
                        
                     </msItem>
                     
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <locus from="190r" to="210r"/>
                        <title type="complete" ref="LIT1828Mahale">Maḥālǝya nabiyāt ‘The Canticles of the Prophets’</title>
                        <colophon xml:lang="gez" xml:id="coloph2">
                           <locus target="#210r"/>
                           ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘአቡነ፡ <del rend="effaced"/> ሥላሴ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለ<del rend="effaced"/> ወልዱ፡ ሰብሐት፡ ለአብ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MV"/> ኦእግዚኦ፡ ዕቀቦ፡ ለገብርከ፡ <del rend="effaced"/> ወለወልዱ፡ ወ<del rend="effaced"/> እለ፡
                           አዕረፉ፡ በርትዕት፡ ሃይማኖት፡ አዕርፍ፡ እግዚኦ፡ ነፍሳተ፡ አበዊነ፡ ገብረ፡ <supplied reason="lost" cert="medium">እግዚእ፡ (?)</supplied> <del rend="effaced"/>
                           <note>It is written at the end of the Canticles in black ink. The name of <persName role="donor" ref="PRS15303NewayaSellase"><roleName type="title">ʾAbuna</roleName>
                                 Nǝwāya Śǝllāse</persName> has been partly erased. The name of the church to which he donated the book has been also erased. The prayer
                           is almost identical to the supplication and <ref target="coloph1"/> quoted above. The name of the supplicant
                              <persName ref="PRS15304GabraEgzi"><roleName type="title">ʾAbuna</roleName> Gabra ʾƎgziʾ</persName> (?) is partly erased; it was probably written by the same
                              secondary hand as the supplication and <ref target="coloph1"/> quoted above, in reddish-brown ink.</note> 
                        </colophon>
                     </msItem>
                     
