                           <item><ref target="#ms_i1.5"/>
                              <list>
                           <item>The abbreviation stands for the whole refrain:</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ወበእንተዝ፡</abbr> for <expan>ወበእንተዝ፡ ናዓብየኪ፡ ኵልነ፡ ኦእግዝእትነ፡ ወላዲተ፡
                                 አምላክ፡ ንጽሕት፡ ኵሎ፡ ጊዜ፡ ንስእል፡ ወናንቀዓዱ፡ ከመ፡ ንርከብ፡ ሣህለ፡ በኀበ፡ መፍቀሬ፡ ሰብእ፡</expan> (<locus from="257rb" to="262vb"/>)</item>
                              </list>
                           </item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names (name of St Mary in <ref target="#ms_i1.4"/>, <ref target="#ms_i1.5"/> and <ref target="#ms_i1.4"/>, <ref target="#ms_i2"/>); 
                           titles and numbers of the Psalms, Canticles and Songs; incipit of
                           each Psalm of the Virgin; title of <ref target="#ms_i1.2"/>, <ref target="#ms_i1.3"/> and <ref target="#ms_i1.2"/>, <ref target="#ms_i1.5"/>; title and
                           incipit of the daily readings of <ref target="#ms_i1.4"/>; refrains of <ref target="#ms_i1.4"/> and <ref target="#ms_i1.5"/>
                           (written out fully or abbreviated); name, number and traditional
                           interpretation of the Hebrew letters in Psalm 118; a few other words in
                           <ref target="#ms_i1.4"/> and <ref target="#ms_i1.5"/>; elements of the punctuation marks and text dividers;
                           Ethiopic numerals or their elements. Two groups of lines on
                           the incipit page of <ref target="#ms_i1.1"/> and <ref target="#ms_i1.4"/>.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#221v"/>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">(above) Donation note, written in the same secondary hand as reddish-brown parts of
                              the supplication on  <locus target="#122v"/>, <ref target="#coloph1"/> and <ref target="#coloph2"/>. It mentions 
                              <persName ref="PRS15304GabraEgzi">Gabra ʾƎgziʾ</persName>, his father <persName ref="PRS15312KenfaGab">Kǝnfa
                                 Gabrǝʾel</persName>, his mother <persName ref="PRS15313WalattaSellase">Walatta Śǝllāse</persName>, his brothers 
                              <persName ref="PRS15314GabraIyasus">Gabra ʾIyasus</persName> and <persName ref="PRS15315WaldaTakHay">Walda Takla Hāymānot</persName> and his sisters 
                              <persName ref="PRS15316WalattaKidan">Walatta Kidān</persName>, <persName ref="PRS15317WalattaEgzi">Walatta ʾƎgziʾ</persName> and
                              <persName ref="PRS15318AmataSeyon">ʾAmata Ṣǝyon</persName>. The name of  <persName ref="PRS15304GabraEgzi">Gabra ʾƎgziʾ</persName> was erased. 
                              The note is encircled with a thin line.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"> <del rend="effaced"/> <hi rend="rubric">ገብረ፡ እግዚእ፡</hi> አቡሁ፡ <hi rend="rubric">ክንፈ፡ ገብርኤል፡</hi>
                              ወእሙ፡ <hi rend="rubric">ወለተ፡ ሥላሴ፡</hi> ወአኃዊሁ፡ <hi rend="rubric">ገብረ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ወልደ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡</hi> ወአኃቲሁ፡ <hi rend="rubric">ወለተ፡ ኪዳን፡ ወለተ፡ እግዚእ፡ አመተ፡ ጽዮን፡</hi></q>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#221v"/>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">(below) Donation note, written in small letters with big
                              forked serifs of vowel markers, in black ink. It mentions <persName role="donor" ref="PRS15305GabraMaryam"><roleName type="title">ʾAbuna</roleName> Gabra Māryām</persName> 
                              as the donor of the manuscript to the church of <placeName ref="INS0174MAKM">Kidāna Mǝḥrat Māy ʾAnbasā</placeName>. 
                              It also mentions his father <persName ref="PRS15306GabraKidan">Gabra Kidān</persName>, his mother
                              <persName ref="PRS15307AmataMikael">ʾAmata Mikāʾel</persName>, his brother <persName ref="PRS15308WaldaAnanya">Walda ʾAnānyā</persName>, 
                              his sisters <persName ref="PRS15309SabanaGiyorgis">Sabana Giyorgis</persName>, <persName ref="PRS15310WalattaTakHay">Walatta Takla Hāymānot</persName> and 
                              <persName ref="PRS15311HirutaSellase">Ḥiruta Śǝllāse</persName> (cp. <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmakm007"/>). </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ዝ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘአቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘተሣየጦ፡
                              በወርቁ፡ ወሀባ፡ ለኪዳነ፡ ምሕረት፡ ዘማየ፡ አንበሳ፡ ከመ፡ ታድኅኖ። እምነ፡ ጌጋይ፡ ወአበሳ፡ ስመ፡ አቡሁ፡
                              ገብረ፡ ኪዳን፡ ወስመ፡ ዕሙ፡ አመተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወእሁሁ፡ ወልደ፡ አናንያ፡ ወአሀቲሁ፡ ሰበነ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ወለተ፡
                              ተክለ፡ ሀይማኖት፡ ሒሩተ፡ ሥላሴ። ዘሰረቆ፡ ወዘፈሀቆ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡</q>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <locus target="#112r"/>
                           <desc>Shelfmark C4-IV-9</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <locus target="#93r"/>
                           <desc>The midpoint of the ‘Psalms of David’ (in Psalm 77) is marked with the words <foreign xml:lang="gez">መንፈቀ፡ ዳዊት፡</foreign> (‘the middle of Dāwit’), written in a
                              secondary hand in alternating black and red ink and framed in a circle.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <locus target="#246r"/>
                           <desc>Three magic names: <foreign xml:lang="gez">አልጸኖን</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">አዴኖን</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢያቡስቴ</foreign> are written in a very
                             small script, in the intercolumn margin, with thin lines above and below.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <locus target="#97r #143v #159v #217r"/>
                           <desc>The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting to accommodate the end of the line or strophe. The folia listed above are a few examples.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <locus target="#2r #31r #63r #99v #131v #144v #159v #214v #229r"/>
                           <desc>Part of the line is taken up. The folia listed above are a few examples.</desc> 
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <locus target="#34r #42v #91v #104r #172v"/>
                           <desc>Part of the line is taken down.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e7">
                           <locus target="#18v2 #46v6 #78v17 #81v11 #164v11 #171v15"/> 
                           <desc type="Correction">Tamallas-sign, in the shape of two perpendicular lines, indicating the place where an omitted word, written in the margin, belongs.</desc> 
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e8">
                           <locus target="#16v #71r #96r #164v #191r #223rb #253va"/>
                           <desc type="Correction">Omitted letters and words written interlineally. The folia listed above are a few examples.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e9">
                           <locus target="#18rv #45r #81v #108v #153v #190v #240r"/> 
